HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 227
By Littleton
A RESOLUTION to recognize and honor Melody Corlew Lewis on
the occasion of her retirement.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
specially recognize those estimable Tennesseans who have dedicated themselves to improving
the quality of life for their fellow citizens; and
WHEREAS, Melody Corlew Lewis is one such individual, who, after thirty-five devoted
years of service, took her well-deserved retirement from her position as town recorder for White
Bluff on December 31, 2024; and
WHEREAS, in the early 1990s, Ms. Lewis acquired her Certified Municipal Clerk
designation, and in 2012, she became a Certified Municipal Finance Officer; and
WHEREAS, during her tenure as town recorder, Melody Lewis witnessed the population
growth of White Bluff from 1,200 to over 4,000, which resulted in the flourishing of many long-
term businesses; furthermore, she witnessed the adoption of a Planning and Zoning committee,
which played a crucial role in shaping White Bluff's future; and
WHEREAS, a dedicated citizen, Melody Lewis worked on the CDBG Grant for the
rehabilitation of the sewer lines; the LPRF Grant, which was used to build the ballfields,
concessions, and a walking track at Veteran's Memorial Park; and the HOME Grant, which
allowed the elderly and lower-income communities to refurbish or rebuild their homes; and
WHEREAS, furthermore, Ms. Lewis worked alongside five different mayors during her
tenure, and she helped witness and prepare the paperwork for the sale of beer and liquor by the
drink; and
